# Testing

## Frontend (React Testing Library + Vitest)

- Test user-visible behavior, not implementation details
- Examples: click checkbox → task marked done; delete → snackbar with Undo appears
- Use `screen.getByRole`, `userEvent` — avoid testing internal state or hook calls directly

## Backend (NestJS @nestjs/testing)

- Unit test services: 5-task-per-category limit, validation edge cases
- E2e test endpoints: POST/GET/PATCH/DELETE `/todos`, GET `/categories`

## File conventions

- Name files `*.test.tsx` (frontend) or `*.spec.ts` (backend)
- Colocate next to source or mirror structure in `__tests__/`
